{"title_page": "Rafael Chirbes", "text_new": "'''Rafael Chirbes''' (27 June 1949 \u2013 15 August 2015) was a Spanish novelist.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cultura.elpais.com/cultura/2015/08/15/actualidad/1439657617_135750.html|title=Muere el escritor Rafael Chirbes|date=15 August 2015|publisher=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=15 August 2015}}</ref> He was born in [[Tavernes de la Valldigna]] in [[Valencia]]. He is the author of several novels, two of which have won the [[Premio de la Cr\u00edtica Espa\u00f1ola|Premio de la Cr\u00edtica de narrativa castellana]] - ''Crematorio'' (2007) and ''En la orilla'' (2013). The latter also won the [[Premio Nacional de Narrativa]].\n\nChirbes is further known for his trilogy of novels dealing with postwar Spain (''La larga marcha'', ''La ca\u00edda de Madrid'' and ''Los viejos amigos''). He also wrote several collections of essays.<ref name=\"anagrama-ed\">{{cite web|url=http://www.anagrama-ed.es/autor/237 |title=Rafael Chirbes - Ed. Anagrama. |publisher=[[Anagrama]]|accessdate=2015-08-12}}</ref>\n\nHis 2007 work ''[[Crematorio]]'' was made into an acclaimed television series in 2014.\n\n==Works==\n\n===Novels===\n* ''Mimoun'' (1988)\n* ''En la lucha final'' (1991)\n* ''La buena letra'' (1992)\n* ''Los disparos del cazador'' (1994)\n* ''La larga marcha'' (1996)\n* ''La ca\u00edda de Madrid'' (2000)\n* ''Los viejos amigos'' (2003)\n* ''Crematorio'' (2007)\n* ''En la orilla'' (2013), published as ''On the Edge'' by [[New Directions Publishing|New Directions]] in 2016\n* ''Par\u00eds-Austerlitz'' (2016)\n\n===Essays===\n* ''Mediterr\u00e1neos'' (1997)\n* ''El novelista perplejo'' (2002)\n* ''El viajero sedentario'' (2004)\n* ''Por cuenta propia'' (2010)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2986381}}\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chirbes, Rafael}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish novelists]]\n[[Category:Gay writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from Spain]]\n[[Category:LGBT novelists]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language LGBT writers]]\n", "text_old": "'''Rafael Chirbes''' (27 June 1949 \u2013 15 August 2015) was a Spanish novelist.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cultura.elpais.com/cultura/2015/08/15/actualidad/1439657617_135750.html|title=Muere el escritor Rafael Chirbes|date=15 August 2015|publisher=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=15 August 2015}}</ref> He was born in [[Tavernes de la Valldigna]] in [[Valencia]]. He is the author of several novels, two of which have won the [[Premio de la Cr\u00edtica Espa\u00f1ola|Premio de la Cr\u00edtica de narrativa castellana]] - ''Crematorio'' (2007) and ''En la orilla'' (2013). The latter also won the [[Premio Nacional de Narrativa]].\n\nChirbes is further known for his trilogy of novels dealing with postwar Spain (''La larga marcha'', ''La ca\u00edda de Madrid'' and ''Los viejos amigos''). He also wrote several collections of essays.<ref name=\"anagrama-ed\">{{cite web|url=http://www.anagrama-ed.es/autor/237 |title=Rafael Chirbes - Ed. Anagrama. |publisher=[[Anagrama]]|accessdate=2015-08-12}}</ref>\n\nHis 2007 work ''[[Crematorio]]'' was made into an acclaimed television series in 2014.\n\n==Works==\n\n===Novels===\n* ''Mimoun'' (1988)\n* ''En la lucha final'' (1991)\n* ''La buena letra'' (1992)\n* ''Los disparos del cazador'' (1994)\n* ''La larga marcha'' (1996)\n* ''La ca\u00edda de Madrid'' (2000)\n* ''Los viejos amigos'' (2003)\n* ''Crematorio'' (2007)\n* ''En la orilla'' (2013), published as ''On the Edge'' by [[New Directions Publishing|New Directions]] in 2016\n* ''Par\u00eds-Austerlitz'' (2016)\n\n===Essays===\n* ''Mediterr\u00e1neos'' (1997)\n* ''El novelista perplejo'' (2002)\n* ''El viajero sedentario'' (2004)\n* ''Por cuenta propia'' (2010)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2986381}}\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{DEF