{"title_page": "Ramon Muzones", "text_new": "'''Ramon Muzones''' (March 20, 1913 - August 17, 1992) was a [[writer]] and [[lawyer]] and the posthumous recipient of the [[National Artist of the Philippines]] for Literature award in the [[Philippines]] in 2018.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://philippinesgraphic.net/national-artists-of-2018/|title=National Artists of 2018 \u2013 The Philippines Graphic|last=Philippines_Graphic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> He wrote in [[Hiligaynon language|Hiligaynon]] and popularized [[Hiligaynon literature]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.panaynews.net/ilonggo-writer-muzones-named-national-artist-for-literature/|title=Ilonggo writer Muzones named National Artist for Literature|last=News|first=Panay|date=2018-10-24|website=Panay News|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\nMuzones was born in Iloilo City<ref name=\":0\" /> and was the oldest of ten children of Santiago Muzones and Florentina Larupay. He received his law degree at [[Central Philippine University]] in 1952. He wrote 62 novels in the course of his life, the first of which was Tibud nga Bulawan in 1938.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ncca.gov.ph/about-culture-and-arts/culture-profile/national-artists-of-the-philippines/ramon-muzones/|title=Order of National Artists: Ramon L. Muzones|website=National Commission for Culture and the Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> He was a founder of an organization for Hiligaynon writers called Sumakwelan.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cpu.edu.ph/news/cpu-dlmch-holds-ramon-l-muzones-memorial-lecture/|title=CPU DLMCH holds Ramon L. Muzones Memorial Lecture|last=University|first=Central Philippine|website=Central Philippine University|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n== Writing ==\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Shri-Bishaya (1969)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Malala nga Gutom (Malignant Hunger,1965)<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://visayas.politics.com.ph/ilonggo-ramon-muzones-to-be-named-national-artist/|title=Ilonggo Ramon Muzones to be named National Artist|date=2018-10-24|website=Politiko Visayas|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Babae Batuk sa Kalibutan (Woman Against the World,1959)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Ang Gugma sang Gugma Bayaran (Love with Love Be Paid, 1955)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Si Tamblot (1948)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Margosatubig: The Story of Salagunting (1946)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Awards ==\nMuzones' awards included the Gawad Bonifacio sa Panitikan Centennial Award given by the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (1997).<ref name=\":1\" /> In 2018 he was honored as an Ilonggo National Artist of the Philippines for Literature.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://peoplesdomain.net/happening-today-late-na-for-literature-ramon-l-muzones-to-be-honored/|title=[Happening Today] Late NA for Literature Ramon L. Muzones to be honored \u00bb People's Domain|last=peoplesdomain|date=2019-12-20|website=People's Domain|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Filipino writers]]\n[[Category:National Artists of the Philippines]]\n", "text_old": "'''Ramon Muzones''' (March 20, 1913 - August 17, 1992) was a [[writer]] and [[lawyer]] and the posthumous recipient of the [[National Artist of the Philippines]] for Literature award in the [[Philippines]] in 2018.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://philippinesgraphic.net/national-artists-of-2018/|title=National Artists of 2018 \u2013 The Philippines Graphic|last=Philippines_Graphic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> He wrote in [[Hiligaynon language|Hiligaynon]] and popularized [[Hiligaynon literature]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.panaynews.net/ilonggo-writer-muzones-named-national-artist-for-literature/|title=Ilonggo writer Muzones named National Artist for Literature|last=News|first=Panay|date=2018-10-24|website=Panay News|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\nMuzones was born in Iloilo City<ref name=\":0\" /> and was the oldest of ten children of Santiago Muzones and Florentina Larupay. He received his law degree at [[Central Philippine University]] in 1952. He wrote 62 novels in the course of his life, the first of which was Tibud nga Bulawan in 1938.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ncca.gov.ph/about-culture-and-arts/culture-profile/national-artists-of-the-philippines/ramon-muzones/|title=Order of National Artists: Ramon L. Muzones|website=National Commission for Culture and the Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> He was a founder of an organization for Hiligaynon writers called Sumakwelan.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cpu.edu.ph/news/cpu-dlmch-holds-ramon-l-muzones-memorial-lecture/|title=CPU DLMCH holds Ramon L. Muzones Memorial Lecture|last=University|first=Central Philippine|website=Central Philippine University|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n== Writing ==\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Shri-Bishaya (1969)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Malala nga Gutom (Malignant Hunger,1965)<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://visayas.politics.com.ph/ilonggo-ramon-muzones-to-be-named-national-artist/|title=Ilonggo Ramon Muzones to be named National Artist|date=2018-10-24|website=Politiko Visayas|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Babae Batuk sa Kalibutan (Woman Against the World,1959)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Ang Gugma sang Gugma Bayaran (Love with Love Be Paid, 1955)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Si Tamblot (1948)\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Margosatubig: The Story of Salagunting (1946)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Awards ==\nMuzones' awards included the Gawad Bonifacio sa Panitikan Centennial Award given by the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (1997).<ref name=\":1\" /> In 2018 he was honored as an Ilonggo National Artist of the Philippines for Literature. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://peoplesdomain.net/happening-today-late-na-for-literature-ramon-l-muzones-to-be-honored/|title=[Happening Today] Late NA for Literature Ramon L. Muzones to be honored \u00bb People's Domain|last=peoplesdomain|date=2019-12-20|website=People's Domain|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Filipino writers]]\n[[Category:National Artists of the Philippines]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramon_Muzones"}
